    • Method Detail

      • dequeue

        T dequeue(int x)
   throws EmptyCollectionException,
          InvalidArgumentException
        Removes and returns the element that is at place x in the queue. Precondition: x must be less than 5, x must be less than size Note: indexing from 0: 0 == front element, 1 == second element, etc.
        Parameters:
        x - the passed in index of the element to be removed
        Returns:
        the element removed from the queue
        Throws:
        EmptyCollectionException - if the queue is empty
        InvalidArgumentException - if x > 4, or x > size of collection

      • first

        T first(int x)
 throws EmptyCollectionException,
        InvalidArgumentException
        Returns (without removing) the element that is at place x in the queue. Precondition: x must be less than 5, x must be less than size Note: indexing from 0: 0 == front element, 1 == second element, etc.
        Parameters:
        x - the specified index of the element to return
        Returns:
        the element at the front of the queue
        Throws:
        EmptyCollectionException - if the queue is empty
        InvalidArgumentException - if x > 4, or x > size of collection
